    {
      "paragraph_name": "PAUTBPCB",
      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This copybook defines the structure of PAUTBPCB, which appears to be related to IMS database interaction, specifically with a PCB (Program Communication Block). The structure includes fields such as PAUT-DBDNAME (database name), PAUT-SEG-LEVEL (segment level), PAUT-PCB-STATUS (PCB status), and PAUT-PCB-PROCOPT (processing options) which are standard elements found in IMS PCBs. It also contains fields for PAUT-SEG-NAME (segment name), PAUT-KEYFB-NAME (key feedback name), PAUT-NUM-SENSEGS (number of sensitive segments), and PAUT-KEYFB (key feedback area). The FILLER field is used for padding or alignment purposes. This copybook is likely included in COBOL programs that interact with an IMS database to access and manipulate data within the database segments. The PAUT-KEYFB field is a 255-byte field that likely holds the key feedback information after an IMS database call.",
